px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3841630" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC.-Credit-PRESS.jpg" alt="BGWMC。信用：出版" width="3000" height="1395" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC.-Credit-PRESS.jpg 3000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC.-Credit-PRESS-400x186.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC.-Credit-PRESS-800x372.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC.-Credit-PRESS-696x324.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC.-Credit-PRESS-1392x647.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC.-Credit-PRESS-1068x497.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 3000px) 100vw, 3000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3841630" class="wp-caption-text"> BGWMC。信用：出版</figcaption></figure><p>伯特纳尔绿色工作男子俱乐部是英国受到威胁的无数基层场所之一。 MVT已经警告说， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-venue-trust-annual-report-government-action-arena-investment-frank-turner-talent-pipeline-3389434">该国的演出空间在没有紧急政府行动的情况下“越过悬崖”</a> 。</p><p>例如，到2023年底，有一个明显的警告指出， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/uk-to-lose-10-per-cent-of-grassroots-venues-in-2023-as-calls-grow-for-rest-of-industry-to-invest-3499727">英国将损失10％的基层音乐场所</a>，而MVT结束了这一年<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/2023-was-worst-year-for-venue-closures-while-no-one-in-music-industry-seems-to-care-say-mvt-3562266">，告诉NME 2023年《 2023年》是“场地关闭最糟糕的一年”，</a>而“音乐产业中没有人似乎都在乎”。</p><p>这些问题也加入了2024年，并在1月份<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/report-shows-disaster-facing-grassroots-music-venues-the-big-companies-and-arenas-are-now-going-to-have-to-answer-for-this-3576307">发表了一份新报告，显示“灾难”在2023年袭击了英国的基层音乐场所</a>。其中的主要发现是，125个英国场地放弃了现场音乐，其中一半以上完全关闭了 - <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/legendary-music-venue-moles-in-bath-closes-after-45-years-today-is-a-very-sad-day-3553756">包括巴斯的传奇痣</a>。</p><p>特色艺术家联盟的首席执行官戴维·马丁（David Martin）在2月进一步强调了音乐家和场地所有者所面临的斗争，当时他谈到了<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/artsists-audiences-need-saving-too-venues-fac-featured-coalition-3584454">基层场地的迅速下降，对英国人才造成了巨大损害</a>。 </p><figure id="attachment_3841632" aria-describedby="caption-attachment-3841632" style="width: 2000px" class="wp-caption alignnone"><img loading="lazy" decoding="async" class="size-full wp-image-3841632" src="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC-Save-Our-Venue.-Credit-PRESS-2.jpg" alt="BGWMC-保存我们的场地。信用：出版" width="2000" height="1270" srcset="https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC-Save-Our-Venue.-Credit-PRESS-2.jpg 2000w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC-Save-Our-Venue.-Credit-PRESS-2-400x254.jpg 400w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC-Save-Our-Venue.-Credit-PRESS-2-800x508.jpg 800w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC-Save-Our-Venue.-Credit-PRESS-2-696x442.jpg 696w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC-Save-Our-Venue.-Credit-PRESS-2-1392x884.jpg 1392w, https://www.nme.com/wp-content/uploads/2025/02/BGWMC-Save-Our-Venue.-Credit-PRESS-2-1068x678.jpg 1068w" sizes="auto, (max-width: 2000px) 100vw, 2000px" /><figcaption id="caption-attachment-3841632" class="wp-caption-text"> BGWMC  - 保存我们的场地。信用：出版</figcaption></figure><p>最近， <em>NME</em>报道了政府如何开始干预， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/government-back-arena-ticket-levy-to-save-grassroots-music-but-urgent-deadline-is-needed-to-prevent-an-even-gloomier-future-3812464">文化，媒体和体育委员会欢迎政府对竞技场及以上演出征税的新支持，以保护基层。</a></p><p>此举是由<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/music-venue-trust-coldplay-ticket-money-donation-interview-3798462">Coldplay</a>之类的人实施的，它看到了一部分是由大型旅行赚取的钱来帮助确保较小场所的未来的一部分， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-case-has-been-made-for-a-1-ticket-levy-on-all-arena-gigs-for-the-survival-of-grassroots-venues-and-artists-3611533">进入Shikari</a> ， <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/katy-perry-announces-lifetimes-2025-uk-tour-donating-to-music-venue-trust-buy-tickets-3813601">Katy Perry</a>和<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/sam-fender-announces-uk-european-people-watching-tour-buy-tickets-3803992">Sam Fender</a></p><p>在MVT争辩说，由于<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/the-uk-autumn-budget-music-industry-reacts-with-venues-and-nightclubs-at-risk-3808036">最近的预算宣布，</a>巡回演出和艺术家<a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/uk-grassroots-music-venues-touring-collapse-mvt-steve-lamacq-budget-help-3808675">已经遭受了“巡回演出的完全崩溃</a>”，这一势头势头会威胁到英国音乐界的结构。</p><p>委员会主席Caroline Dinenage MP在给国务卿Lisa Nandy的信中写道：“我们当地社区中的大量场所被迫关闭商店，这使艺术家，推动者和其他从事基层音乐的斗争的现实陷入了困境。” “有警告更令人沮丧的未来。”</p><p>作为回应，音乐场所信托基金会首席执行官马克·戴维德（Mark Davyd）告诉<em>NME</em> ，虽然“在该委员会的工作中有大量庆祝”和政府对其的回应，但迪纳尼奇坚持对变革时间表的坚持必须进行。</p><p>他告诉<em>NME</em> ：“由于这一询问，当我们的基层音乐界对其文化，社会和经济价值以及影响力得到适当尊重时，我们现在可以看到一个明确的日期。” “现场音乐生态系统的重大积极变化，无论是通过基层贡献，商业利率审查还是政府的新投资和所有权方法引起的机会。”</p><p> <a href="https://www.nme.com/news/music/fighting-fund-crowdfunder-launched-to-save-bethnal-green-working-mens-club-3841593">“战斗基金”宣传众筹是为了拯救贝丝绿色工作男子俱乐部而发起的，</a>首先出现在<a href="https://www.nme.com">NME</a>上。</p> ;
